user.biography:
A game about placing blocks and going on adventures. Create! Explore! Survive! Here’s how you do it!
ESRB Rating: Everyone 10+ with Fantasy Violence

node.text: A peaceful tree house. A refreshing melon slice. Dancing parrots in the soft glow of a gorgeous sunset. Those are not just three excellent band names – they’re also proof that paradise is just a vine climb away!

node.text: Ah, that most marvellous of mazes! Though danger may be lurking around every corner, it does have an oddly familiar comfort to it, doesn't it?

node.text: Some say schools of frozen fish sticks scurry freely underneath the ice. We say: let’s build a hut, carve a hole, and find out!

node.text: On and on we go! Though the light at the end of the tunnel seems far away at times, no one can stop us from moving ever-forward!

node.text: It takes honour and valiance to face your foes atop the battlements – but it’s a lot more efficient to just build a few arrow dispensers into your castle walls!

node.text: Whether it’s a tower, a castle, or your very own personal realm, this is certainly a place you can proudly call home!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Minecraft on July 21, 2021. May be a cartoon.

node.text:
We know, those amethyst geodes look like they formed through ages of mineral deposition, but they actually emerged from the hands of a talented team of artists and developers! 

Back when Caves & Cliffs was first taking shape, concept artist @mariana.salimena made these beautiful explorations of what underground crystals might look like:

node.text: As the old saying goes: you don’t truly appreciate what you have until you’re being ruthlessly hunted down by a vicious phantom! A soft bed; an even softer cat – solid ground, even!

node.text: Building a house? Pah! In the Mushroom Fields, your next lodging might just sprout from the soil - and nobody will notice if you smell a little fungi!

node.text: Crawl, baby turtle, crawl! That ravenous army of drowned will stop at nothing in their quest for a tasty midnight snack – except for an early sunrise, that is!
